snippet.textDisplay:
Here this bloke Ornob goes again. He has ruined the sanity, uniqueness and sagacity of our genious social reformer and philosopher of a 'saiji's' creation of  'Lalon geeti' of the highest order in the name of fusion. Why on earth one need to fuse Lalan geeti with anything else? Why? Lalon geeti has its own uniqueness. Nobody has the right to destroy its uniqueness. Who is Ornob trying to do that? What is he upto? So much so, the lady singer has been attired in a wierd dress which is totally allien to our folk culture.
Look at IPDC productions directed by Partha Barua. That is called world- class musical 
 production. We have failed to understand what Coke Studio is upto. We are watching with great regret how Calcacians have developed an obsession for Hindi. The other day, I was watching Debolina's masterpiece presentation of our genious poet's -Rudra Mohammad Shahidullah-   rendition of 'aamar vetor o bahire...' . This has been an world class presentation but has totally been spoiled by fusing hindi lyrics into it. Is Ornob trying to do the same?  Bewildered and dis- grantled  Calcasian listeners  are now glued to Gaan Baangla, Seylon Musical Videos and IPDC to get rid of brindled Bangla songs hijacked by Hindi songs. Bangladesh is the last hope of preserving rich and unique  Bangla country musical creations of ours. Ornob and company cannot be allowed to destroy our incredibly rich folk tradition.
